<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,907,1221]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Karyotype: 2n = 80 and FN = 86. Autosomal complement: four small metacentric pairs, and 35 acrocentric pairs (one distinctly large and the remaining large to small decreasing in size). Sex chromosomes: X, a very large subtelocentric; Y, a small acrocentric (
<bibRefCitation author="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L." box="[492,756,1015,1041]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref67114" refString="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L. (1976) Karyotypic variation in Oryzomyine rodents (Cricetinae) with comments on chromosomal evolution in the Neotropical Cricetine complex. Occasional papers of the Museum of Zoology, 49, 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1976">Gardner &amp; Patton 1976</bibRefCitation>
, pp. 4, 
<figureCitation box="[834,918,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,1069,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-342@4.[159,1429,1062,1950]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Collection localities of Oryzomyini species analyzed in this work. (1) Claúdia, Mato Grosso state; (2) and (3) Rio Japurá, Amazonas state; (4) and (5) Rio Içá, Amazonas state." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423617" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423617/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Patton, J. L. &amp; Silva, M. N. &amp; Malcolm, J. R." box="[929,1128,1015,1041]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 306" refId="ref71077" refString="Patton, J. L., Silva, M. N. &amp; Malcolm, J. R. (2000) Mammals of the Rio Jurua and the evolutionary and ecological diversification of Amazonia. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 244, 1 - 306. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2000) 244 % 3 C 0001: MOTRJA % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2000">
Patton 
<emphasis box="[1006,1054,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">et al</emphasis>
. 2000
</bibRefCitation>
). A different morphology of sex chromosomes was reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Volobouev, V. T. &amp; Aniskin, V. M." box="[545,874,1051,1077]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="295 - 304" refId="ref74775" refString="Volobouev, V. T. &amp; Aniskin, V. M. (2000) Comparative chromosome banding analysis of three South American species of rice rats of the genus Oryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae). Chromosome Research, 8, 295 - 304. https: // doi. org / 10.1023 / A: 1009223210737" type="journal article" year="2000">Volobouev &amp; Aniskin (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, a submetacentric X and a metacentric Y chromosome. C-banding metaphases exhibited blocks of constitutive heterochromatin on the pericentromeric region of all autosomes. The short arm of X and the Y were entirely heterochromatic. G-banding was also performed (
<bibRefCitation author="Volobouev, V. T. &amp; Aniskin, V. M." pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="295 - 304" refId="ref74775" refString="Volobouev, V. T. &amp; Aniskin, V. M. (2000) Comparative chromosome banding analysis of three South American species of rice rats of the genus Oryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae). Chromosome Research, 8, 295 - 304. https: // doi. org / 10.1023 / A: 1009223210737" type="journal article" year="2000">Volobouev &amp; Aniskin 2000</bibRefCitation>
). FISH with telomeric sequences revealed signals exclusively at the ends of all chromosome arms and no interstitial signals were observed (
<bibRefCitation author="Silva, M. J. J. &amp; Percequillo, A. R. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y." box="[616,806,1195,1221]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="219 - 226" refId="ref73592" refString="Silva, M. J. J., Percequillo, A. R. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. (2000) Cytogenetics and systematic approach on a new Oryzomys species, of the nitidus group (Sigmodontinae, Rodentia) from Northeastern Brazil. Caryologia, 53, 219 - 226. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00087114.2000.10589199" type="journal article" year="2000">
Silva 
<emphasis box="[682,731,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">et al</emphasis>
. 2000
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
